  I've recently started reading as many guides and posts on rogues as I can. After reading a few, I found a question came to mind. Which is a better range choice, bows and arrows or throwing weapons? Perhaps both?<br>
  I know rogues will score critical hits with throwing weapons and get an even larger bonus when facing the back, but throwing weapons fall short on range and damage. The alternative, bows and arrows, tend to have better range and damage, but much slower delay.<br>
  There are also another factor which influences this choice namely cost. Assuming this is on Sullon Zek, where I recently rolled up my new rogue, throwing weapons are cheap in an environment where money (for me anyways) is scarce.<br>
  So I ask for your advice as to which path I should take.<br>
<br>
  Also, I wanted to ask your opinions on my starting stats (I know it's been done to death, but I'll ask anyways). I’m a wood elf rogue with starting stats as: <br>
90 stamina<br>
70 strength<br>
105 agility<br>
90 dexterity<br>
80 wisdom<br>
75 intelligence<br>
75 charisma<br>
<br>
Will this fit well on a pvp server, or should I do something else?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance,<br>
Nily <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/9/01 3:11:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More questions from an inexperienced rogue.</span><hr size=1> i would choose a bow because throwing weapons catch DS dammage, and bows do not.  once you get the money practice in both, and stacks of shurikens are nice caus you CAN interupt casters after they root you, and i dunno if bows can do it to tell the truth.  both would be best, but if i had to pick one i would chose a bow, not only for the no DS, but for the great range. <p><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=86678>Liringlas Lookinglass</a><br>
